# =============================================================================
# DockBack — public release repository (closed source, image-only).
#
# DEFAULT-DENY: nothing is published unless explicitly allow-listed below.
# This keeps the source code, secrets, internal docs, and dev tooling OUT of the
# public repo. Users pull the ready-built multi-arch image from GHCR — they never
# build from source.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore everything at the repository root by default...
/*

# ...then publish ONLY these run + marketing artifacts:
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/SECURITY.md
!/.env.example
!/docker-compose.yml
!/deploy/
!/screenshots/

# Belt-and-suspenders: never publish these even if the rules above change.
# (Secrets, local state, internal material, source, and dev/prod tooling.)
.env
*.env
!.env.example
.claude/
docs/
backup/
data/
backups/
*.db
*.sqlite*
*.key
*.pem
*.age
docker-compose.dev.yml
docker-compose.prod.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
Makefile
go.mod
go.sum
main.go
internal/
frontend/
scripts/
.github/
renovate.json5
.grype.yaml
.trivyignore
node_modules/
